{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 20:10:32.197262", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary\n- Detected anomaly: End-to-end connectivity between host pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24) and host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24) is broken. The fabric is missing a route to 10.0.1.0/24.\n- Fault localization: leaf_router_0_1 is not advertising its directly connected subnet 10.0.1.0/24 into BGP.\n- Root cause: Misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_1—no “network 10.0.1.0/24” (or equivalent redistribution) under BGP, so 10.0.1.0/24 is never injected into EBGP, and thus unknown to upstream devices and to leaf_router_0_0.\n\nEvidence and Tests\n\n1) Host-to-host reachability\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 100% loss with “Destination Net Unreachable” generated by 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0). This indicates leaf_router_0_0 has no route to 10.0.1.0/24.\n- pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: Timed out within tool limit; consistent with asymmetric reachability because the return path (to 10.0.1.0/24) is missing on leaf_router_0_0.\n\n2) Routing tables on leaves and spines\n- leaf_router_0_0 routes:\n  - Has connected 10.0.0.0/24 and many BGP routes, but 10.0.1.0/24 is absent.\n- leaf_router_0_1 routes:\n  - Has connected 10.0.1.0/24, and BGP routes to many other subnets; however, 10.0.1.0/24 is not present in its BGP table (only as kernel connected).\n- spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, super_spine_router_0:\n  - None have a route to 10.0.1.0/24. They do have routes to 10.0.0.0/24 and various other subnets.\n\n3) BGP session health\n- All EBGP sessions reported up across the fabric (leafs to spines, spines to super-spine).\n- spine_router_0_0 shows PfxRcd=0 from leaf_router_0_1 (neighbor 172.16.0.35), while spine_router_0_1 shows PfxRcd=7 from leaf_router_0_1 (neighbor 172.16.0.43). Regardless, neither spine has 10.0.1.0/24, which aligns with leaf_router_0_1 not originating it.\n\n4) BGP advertisements from leaf_router_0_1\n- show ip bgp neighbors … advertised-routes from leaf_router_0_1 to spines lists seven prefixes, but 10.0.1.0/24 is missing.\n- show ip bgp on leaf_router_0_1 likewise does not include 10.0.1.0/24 as a locally originated prefix.\n\n5) BGP configuration comparison\n- leaf_router_0_0:\n  - router bgp 65200 … address-family ipv4 unicast; network 10.0.0.0/24 (present)\n- leaf_router_0_1:\n  - router bgp 65201 … neighbors defined, but no address-family stanza advertising network 10.0.1.0/24 and no redistribution configured.\n  - Thus, 10.0.1.0/24 stays as connected-only and is not injected into BGP.\n\nImpact\n- Any traffic destined to 10.0.1.0/24 from the rest of the fabric is dropped at the first hop lacking a route (e.g., leaf_router_0_0), causing “Destination Net Unreachable.”\n- pc_0_1 can forward traffic towards 10.0.0.0/24 (its leaf has routes), but return traffic to 10.0.1.0/24 fails, breaking practical end-to-end connectivity.\n\nAdditional Observations\n- Asymmetry: spine_router_0_0 shows zero prefixes received from leaf_router_0_1 while spine_router_0_1 shows seven. This does not change the primary diagnosis (10.0.1.0/24 is missing entirely from leaf_router_0_1’s advertised set), but indicates a secondary inconsistency in received routes on spine_router_0_0.\n\nConclusion\n- The network fabric is generally healthy at the session level (BGP adjacencies up), but the critical 10.0.1.0/24 subnet is not being originated into BGP at leaf_router_0_1. This misconfiguration is the root cause of the observed host-to-host connectivity failure.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 17126, "output_tokens": 5280, "total_tokens": 22406, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 12032}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 4224}}}
